USA: Repetition is mother of cleverness
It's almost weird with what student aspiration Barack Obama, the president with his reputation of the smartest, repeats his predecessor's strategy on the Afghanistan issue, which he himself considered the dumbest.
When he finally sweated out his eagerly awaited Afghanistan doctrine, it turned out that he wrote them off via the copy paper from the bush-Iraq scenario three years ago.
Not only did he use the phrase "as in Iraq" in the text himself several times, he even used the name of the Bush Declaration of January 2007 as the name of his own declaration: "New Forward" without hesitation.
Three years ago, he himself criticized the Bush idea - to send out fresh troop quotas to Iraq plagued by the civil war - as an "irresponsible and in its conclusions carastrophic decision."
The following months showed, however, that the Bush strategy, which was made by recommendations of the military, was the only possible and very successful in so far as that today the news about Iraq is no longer spoken at all.
Bush's reputation was not improved by this, because objectively he left his successor a much more grateful initial situation than was to be expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will repeat itself.
The military has again asked him to increase the contingent of troops, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghanistan operation General Stanley McCristal, who even harshly criticized the hesitant shooters in the White House despite the subordination habits.
He called for 40,000 troops to reverse the situation for the better.
The president hesitated for three months but has come up with no better idea and so he has cheated the general at least around 10,000 troops.
From Europe, he has pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even if he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
The very problem with the whole Obama strategy is his intention to withdraw the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this process within three years. The whole Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even despite the brotherly war of recent years, Iraq society is relatively well structured, its leaders honoring the values.
The Afghan situation is marked by the contraindication - you can rely on nobody and no agreements are kept.
Under these conditions, it is hard to prepare the Afghan security forces who are accustomed to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally founded correctly, remain only sham buildings, behind which the patriarchal tribal relations will continue to proliferate.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the complexity of the conditions that further complicate the Pakistan and Iran influences.
Also, building a "capable state" that is the minimalist goal of the whole operation is very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama strategy alienated by its voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only continued to deteriorate and now it is on the verge of the explosion.
Believe that the little soldiers who have broken out into the war cry over the "early return" create a miracle here, can only a truly romantic soul, which is not impressed by facts.
From the political point of view, the date for the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, because the Taliban will take that as the indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of the Europeans to participate in the battles in Afghanistan is running out.
Europe's politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is related to the war in the Hindu Kush Mountains foreland.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
Should the situation continue to deteriorate and the increased sanctions on the Iranians do not work, there is a very serious question for the United States whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question must be answered in the period when America is moving to Obama for the winning withdrawal from Afghanistan.
But any solution will also mean a dramatic turn of the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that there are still three years until the presidential election, and thus there is still enough time for him to resort to a different strategy, if it would prove to be a total failure.
