The connection between delusion and dream has occupied philosophers and physicians since ancient times.
Aristotle understood hallucinations as a form of dream in the awake state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychiatry, stated in 1861 a "great similarity of being insane with dream states," for Sigmund Freud the dream was even "a psychosis, with all inconsistencies, delusions, sensory illusions of such".
