Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and preparation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified on the basis of the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables, such as the price for the working hours, surcharges or discounts and after that he can have the cost estimate printed out and passed on to his customer.
AudaTaller, however, is not a tool for appraisal such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not involve estimated working hours.
The cost of use for this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
The company Audatex is currently working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for for a long time, because you can choose a door with it, for example, and and then completely turn the picture around to look at the inside.
